Document: PhysicsMaterial  
Path: godot/classes/class_physicsmaterial.rst  
Summary: Properties and methods for configuring physics material behavior in Godot, including bounce, friction, and collision absorption settings.  

absorbent (bool): If true, subtracts the bounciness from the colliding object's bounciness instead of adding it. Default: false. Methods: set_absorbent(value: bool) → void, is_absorbent() → bool.  

bounce (float): The body's bounciness. Values range from 0 (no bounce) to 1 (full bounciness). Default: 0.0. Methods: set_bounce(value: float) → void, get_bounce() → float. Note: Even with bounce set to 1.0, energy loss occurs due to linear and angular damping. To preserve energy, set bounce to 1.0, linear/angualr damp modes to Replace, and damp values to 0.0.  

friction (float): The body's friction. Values range from 0 (frictionless) to 1 (maximum friction). Default: 1.0. Methods: set_friction(value: float) → void, get_friction() → float.  

rough (bool): If true, uses the friction of the "rough" object during collisions. If false, uses the lowest friction of colliding objects. If both objects are rough, uses the highest friction. Default: false. Methods: set_rough(value: bool) → void, is_rough() → bool.